But there's a first time for everything.

1872
02:13:27,709 --> 02:13:30,753
I have no further questions.
Thank you, Father.

1873
02:13:32,672 --> 02:13:35,425
WEISMAN: Thank you, Father.
You may step down.

1874
02:13:42,306 --> 02:13:46,227
SHAKES: I've never recovered from seeing
Father Bobby take the stand and lie for us,

1875
02:13:46,310 --> 02:13:48,646
to even the score for John and Tommy.

1876
02:13:49,439 --> 02:13:53,026
He didn't just testify for them,
he testified against Wilkinson

1877
02:13:53,109 --> 02:13:55,903
and the evil that had lived there for too long.

1878
02:13:55,987 --> 02:13:58,573
Still, I was sorry he had to do it.

1879
02:14:05,163 --> 02:14:08,166
With respect to the charge of murder
in the second degree,

1880
02:14:08,249 --> 02:14:12,045
do you find the defendant,
John Reilly, guilty or not guilty?

1881
02:14:12,128 --> 02:14:13,379
Not guilty.

1882
02:14:13,463 --> 02:14:16,340
With respect to the charge of murder
in the second degree,

1883
02:14:16,424 --> 02:14:20,720
do you find the defendant,
Thomas Marcano, guilty or not guilty?

1884
02:14:20,970 --> 02:14:22,221
FOREWOMAN; Not guilty.

1885
02:14:22,305 --> 02:14:25,892
WEISMAN: Thank you very much.
This jury is discharged.

1886
02:14:47,080 --> 02:14:49,874
Hi, how are you? Could I get a hot dog?

1887
02:14:50,583 --> 02:14:54,295
Mustard and relish. A lot of relish.

1888
02:14:57,632 --> 02:14:59,550
Give him two napkins.

1889
02:15:04,806 --> 02:15:06,974
You did good in there, Counselor.

1890
02:15:08,893 --> 02:15:12,522
-What happens to you now?
-What happens? I walk away.

1891
02:15:14,315 --> 02:15:17,110
I'll wait a few weeks, I'll hand in my notice.

1892
02:15:17,193 --> 02:15:19,779
After the way I handled this case,

1893
02:15:19,862 --> 02:15:22,740
they won't be in a rush
to keep me from the door.

1894
02:15:24,909 --> 02:15:29,455
So you switch to the other side and work
as a defense lawyer. The money's better.

1895
02:15:29,956 --> 02:15:33,459
There's always gonna be
more bad guys than good, Mikey.

1896
02:15:34,460 --> 02:15:38,131
And can you imagine the work you'd get
from John and Tommy's crew?

1897
02:15:38,214 --> 02:15:40,007
That's a house and a pool.

1898
02:15:42,051 --> 02:15:43,469
Not for me.

1899
02:15:44,387 --> 02:15:46,973
I've seen all the law I want to see.

1900
02:15:47,723 --> 02:15:50,685
-It's time for something else.
-Like what?

1901
02:15:50,893 --> 02:15:53,187
I'll let you know when I know.

1902
02:15:53,271 --> 02:15:55,731
SHAKES: You're too old to play
for the Yankees

1903
02:15:55,815 --> 02:15:57,733
and you're too young to take up golf.

1904
02:15:57,817 --> 02:16:02,405
Why are you shooting holes through
all my plans? You're gonna make me panic.

1905
02:16:02,488 --> 02:16:04,699
You'll work it out. You always have.

1906
02:16:10,246 --> 02:16:12,498
It's time for quiet, Shakes.

1907
02:16:14,083 --> 02:16:18,004
I just want to shut my eyes
and not have to see the places I've been.

1908
02:16:20,298 --> 02:16:21,549
I'm weary.

1909
02:16:25,428 --> 02:16:26,846
I don't know.

1910
02:16:29,640 --> 02:16:32,351
Maybe I'll get lucky, forget I was even there.

1911
02:16:33,519 --> 02:16:36,022
Don't disappear on me, Counselor.

1912
02:16:37,148 --> 02:16:40,359
-I may need a good lawyer one day.
-You can't afford a good lawyer.

1913
02:16:40,443 --> 02:16:41,944
(LAUGHS)

1914
02:16:43,279 --> 02:16:45,781
I may need a good friend, though.

1915
02:16:47,950 --> 02:16:50,786
I'll find you when you do. Count on it.

1916
02:16:52,830 --> 02:16:54,332
(SOFTLY) Always have.

1917
02:17:00,463 --> 02:17:04,091
SHAKES: A full month had passed since
the acquittal and no one had made contact.

1918
02:17:04,175 --> 02:17:06,552
In those few weeks,
our lives had reverted back

1919
02:17:06,636 --> 02:17:09,805
to what they had been
prior to the murder of Sean Nokes.

1920
02:17:09,889 --> 02:17:12,892
Carol had returned to her stack
of social service files,

1921
02:17:12,975 --> 02:17:15,478
helping troubled teens and single mothers.

1922
02:17:15,561 --> 02:17:19,899
John and Tommy went back to the streets,
running the West Side Boys.

1923
02:17:19,982 --> 02:17:24,612
I was promoted from clerk to reporter
trainee, covering the entertainment beat.

1924
02:17:24,695 --> 02:17:27,156
Michael, as he promised,
resigned from his job

1925
02:17:27,240 --> 02:17:30,326
after working the losing end
of a can't-miss case.

1926
02:17:30,993 --> 02:17:32,411
Excuse me.

1927
02:17:34,747 --> 02:17:37,333
I don't know now to fucking thank you.

1928
02:17:37,458 --> 02:17:39,585
(LAUGHING)

1929
02:17:40,670 --> 02:17:43,923
I can't believe what you did.
I can't believe we got away with it.

1930
02:17:44,006 --> 02:17:46,592
It wasn't me, that was Mikey.
It was all Mikey's plan.

1931
02:17:46,676 --> 02:17:50,137
When I first heard he was taking the case,
I was gonna have him burned.

1932
02:17:50,221 --> 02:17:51,514
Then I figured, he's a friend,

1933
02:17:51,597 --> 02:17:54,225
and if you're sent away for murder,
who better to do it?

1934
02:17:54,350 --> 02:17:56,811
The way he was handling the case,
I thought he sucked.

1935
02:17:56,894 --> 02:17:59,689
I started feeling sorry for the bastard.

1936
02:17:59,772 --> 02:18:02,108
Never feel sorry for a lawyer.

1937
02:18:02,191 --> 02:18:04,277
TOMMY: Get over here, Counselor.

1938
02:18:04,694 --> 02:18:07,029
JOHN: You are the real Count!

1939
02:18:07,280 --> 02:18:10,366
Alive and well, and living in New York City.

1940
02:18:11,701 --> 02:18:13,953
-You fucking maniac.
-All right.

1941
02:18:16,038 --> 02:18:18,124
What is this, a gay bar?

1942
02:18:19,292 --> 02:18:20,835
It was, until you came in.

1943
02:18:20,918 --> 02:18:23,921
Why don't you give me a kiss
to go with that hello?

1944
02:18:29,135 --> 02:18:30,928
Get out of the way.

1945
02:18:36,600 --> 02:18:38,436
Let's have a drink.

1946
02:18:41,731 --> 02:18:43,733
(ALL LAUGHING)

1947
02:18:43,816 --> 02:18:45,401
The Four Gladiators.

1948
02:18:47,611 --> 02:18:50,573
Worst quartet to ever hold
a Hell's Kitchen corner.

1949
02:18:50,656 --> 02:18:53,284
But what was that name
that Shakes wanted to call it?

1950
02:18:53,409 --> 02:18:56,245
Genius wanted to call it
"The Count and His Cristos."

1951
02:18:56,329 --> 02:18:58,998
-Nice!
-TOMMY: It's so sweet, isn't it?

1952
02:18:59,081 --> 02:19:00,166
(ALL LAUGHING)

1953
02:19:00,249 --> 02:19:02,626
TOMMY: That would've sent albums
flying out of the store.

1954
02:19:02,752 --> 02:19:05,421
We weren't that bad.
Some people wanted to hear us sing.

1955
02:19:05,504 --> 02:19:08,341
The kids at the deaf school don't count.

1956
02:19:12,094 --> 02:19:13,971
One song for Carol.

1957
02:19:14,430 --> 02:19:16,640
-I retired a long time ago.
-Come on, you mutts.

1958
02:19:16,766 --> 02:19:18,517
Wait. Don't you guys have to go
and shoot somebody?

1959
02:19:21,812 --> 02:19:22,855
No!

1960
02:19:22,938 --> 02:19:24,231
(ALL LAUGHING)

1961
02:19:24,315 --> 02:19:26,609
We always got time for a song!

1962
02:19:27,610 --> 02:19:30,654
-Just kidding, you know what I'm saying?
-SHAKES: Wine, anybody?

1963
02:19:30,780 --> 02:19:32,907
You pick it, Mikey. Nothing too slow.

1964
02:19:32,990 --> 02:19:34,367
Start us up.

1965
02:19:35,201 --> 02:19:37,036
(HUMMING)

1966
02:19:37,787 --> 02:19:40,039
CAROL: How many songs do you know?
SHAKES: One.

1967
02:19:40,122 --> 02:19:41,665
(ALL LAUGHING)

1968
02:19:42,458 --> 02:19:44,627
(MEN HARMONIZING BADLY)

1969
02:19:45,795 --> 02:19:50,174
(SINGING) Walk like a man

1970
02:19:53,469 --> 02:19:55,471
Walk like a man

1971
02:19:55,554 --> 02:19:57,264
Fast as you can

1972
02:19:57,348 --> 02:20:00,893
Walk like a man, my son

1973
02:20:01,519 --> 02:20:05,022
Go tell the world
Forget about the girl

1974
02:20:05,147 --> 02:20:07,400
Don't forget about the girl.

1975
02:20:17,660 --> 02:20:18,661
(INAUDIBLE)

1976
02:20:21,372 --> 02:20:23,666
SHAKES: On March 16, 1984,

1977
02:20:23,749 --> 02:20:27,294
John Reilly's bloated body was found
face up in a tenement building,

1978
02:20:27,378 --> 02:20:30,214
right next to the bottle of boiler gin
that killed him.

1979
02:20:30,339 --> 02:20:34,468
At the time of his death, he was a suspect
in five unsolved homicides.

1980
02:20:34,552 --> 02:20:37,179
He was two weeks past his 29th birthday.

1981
02:20:41,892 --> 02:20:45,604
Thomas Marcano died on July 26, 1985.

1982
02:20:45,855 --> 02:20:48,232
He was shot at dose range five times.

1983
02:20:48,357 --> 02:20:51,193
The body lay undiscovered
for more than a week.

1984
02:20:51,277 --> 02:20:54,738
There was a crucifix and a picture
of St. Jude in his pocket.

1985
02:20:54,864 --> 02:20:56,782
He was 29 years old.

1986
02:20:58,451 --> 02:21:01,871
Michael Sullivan lives in a small town
in the English countryside,

1987
02:21:01,954 --> 02:21:04,081
where he works part-time as a carpenter

1988
02:21:04,206 --> 02:21:07,251
He no longer practices law,
and he has never married.

1989
02:21:07,877 --> 02:21:09,712
He lives quietly and alone.

1990
02:21:12,465 --> 02:21:16,927
Carol still works for e social service agency
and lives in Hell's Kitchen.

1991
02:21:17,052 --> 02:21:18,304
She has never married,

1992
02:21:18,387 --> 02:21:22,308
but is a single mother
supporting a growing 12-year-old son.

1993
02:21:22,391 --> 02:21:26,729
The boy John Thomas Michael Martinez,
loves to read

1994
02:21:27,062 --> 02:21:29,231
and is called Shakes by his mother

1995
02:21:31,692 --> 02:21:35,613
It was our special night,
and we held it for as long as we could.

1996
02:21:35,738 --> 02:21:37,865
It was our happy ending.

1997
02:21:38,115 --> 02:21:41,535
And the last time
we would ever be together again.

1998
02:21:51,754 --> 02:21:54,548
(INAUDIBLE)

1999
02:22:30,167 --> 02:22:32,461
The future lay sparkling ahead,

2000
02:22:32,586 --> 02:22:35,798
and we thought
we would know each other forever
